[[File:Kawagoe Sanpeninarijinjya Kofun 1.jpg|thumb|right|250px|{{ill|Sanpen Inari Shrine Kofun|ja|三変稲荷神社古墳|12=draft|12=draft}}.]] {{Location map|Japan Saitama Prefecture| label = Senba Kofun Cluster| position = bottom| mark = Red pog.svg| marksize = 10|relief = 1| width = 250| caption={{Left|Location map (coordinates correspond to Jigen-dō Kofun, located within the grounds of {{ill|Kita-in|ja|喜多院|12=draft|12=draft}}).}}}}
'''Senba Kofun Cluster''' (仙波古墳群) is a {{ill|kofun cluster|ja|古墳群|1=Kofun cluster|12=draft|12=draft}} from the early to late {{ill|Kofun period|ja|古墳時代|12=draft|12=draft}}, located around {{ill|Kosennbamachi|ja|小仙波町|12=draft|12=draft}}, {{ill|Kawagoe, Saitama|ja|川越市|12=draft|12=draft}}, {{ill|Saitama Prefecture|ja|埼玉県|12=draft|12=draft}}.
== Overview == The tumuli are distributed mainly along the right bank of the {{ill|Shingashi River|ja|新河岸川|12=draft|12=draft}}, spanning Kosennbamachi, Nishikosennbamachi, Tōmachi, Minamitōmachi, Sugawaramachi, and Fujimimachi. The group surrounding {{ill|Kita-in|ja|喜多院|12=draft|12=draft}} is known as the '''Kosennba Kofun Cluster''', while another group about 2 km away, including the {{ill|Hikawa Shrine Kofun|ja|氷川神社古墳|12=draft|12=draft}}, {{ill|Atago Shrine Kofun|ja|愛宕神社古墳|12=draft|12=draft}}, and {{ill|Asama Shrine Kofun|ja|浅間神社古墳|12=draft|12=draft}}, is distinguished as the '''Daisenba Kofun Cluster'''.
== Major Tumuli == {{OSM Location map | coord = {{Coord|35|54|44.3|N|139|29|28.9|E}} | zoom = 11 | float = right | width = 250| height =250 | caption = Locations of Major Tumuli | scalemark = 60
| mark-coord1= {{Coord|35|55|01.8|N|139|29|22.1|E}} | label1=Jigen-dō Kofun | label-pos1= right | mark-title1=Jigen-dō Kofun | label-size1=13 | label-color1=dark grey | mark-size1=30 | mark1=Red pog.svg
| mark-coord2= {{Coord|35|55|05.2|N|139|29|26.0|E}} | label2=Hie Shrine Kofun | label-pos2= right | mark-title2=Hie Shrine Kofun | label-size1=13 | label-color1=dark grey | mark-size1=30 | mark2=Red pog.svg
| mark-coord3= {{Coord|35|54|54.2|N|139|29|39.76|E}} | label3=Sanpen Inari Shrine Kofun | label-pos3= right | mark-title3=Sanpen Inari Shrine Kofun | label-size3=13 | label-color3=dark grey | mark-size3=30 | mark3=Red pog.svg
| mark-coord4= {{Coord|35|54|21.0|N|139|29|29.9|E}} | label4=Hikawa Shrine Kofun | label-pos4= right | mark-title4=Hikawa Shrine Kofun | label-size4=13 | label-color4=dark grey | mark-size4=30 | mark4=Red pog.svg
| mark-coord5= {{Coord|35|54|17.3|N|139|29|30.0|E}} | label5=Atago Shrine Kofun | label-pos5= right | mark-title5=Atago Shrine Kofun | label-size5=13 | label-color5=dark grey | mark-size5=30 | mark5=Red pog.svg
| mark-coord6= {{Coord|35|54|12.4|N|139|29|20.2|E}} | label6=Asama Shrine Kofun | label-pos6= right | mark-title6=Asama Shrine Kofun | label-size6=13 | label-color6=dark grey | mark-size6=30 | mark6=Red pog.svg }}
=== Kosennba Kofun Cluster === ==== Jigen-dō Kofun ==== Located within {{ill|Kita-in|ja|喜多院|12=draft|12=draft}}'s precincts. The tumulus has been significantly altered due to the presence of {{ill|Jigen-dō|ja|慈眼堂|12=draft|12=draft}}, an Important Cultural Property, and an adjacent cemetery. It currently appears to be a 36-meter-diameter {{ill|round Kofun|ja|円墳|1=Round Kofun|1=Round Kofun|12=draft|12=draft}}, but it may originally have been a {{ill|zenpō-kōen-fun|ja|前方後円墳|1=Zenpokoenfun|12=draft|12=draft}}.
==== Hie Shrine Kofun ==== Located within {{ill|Hie Shrine (Kawagoe, Saitama)|ja|日枝神社 (川越市)|12=draft|12=draft}}'s precincts. Formerly known as the "Tahōtō Kofun" due to a {{ill|tahōtō|ja|多宝塔|1=Tahōtō|12=draft|12=draft}} once being situated atop it. Originally a {{ill|zenpō-kōen-fun|ja|前方後円墳|1=Zenpokoenfun|12=draft|12=draft}}, but the rear circular section was destroyed, leaving only the front portion. Estimated to be built in the mid-6th century.{{Sfn|Kawagoe City Tourism Office|2020}}
==== Sanpen Inari Shrine Kofun ==== {{main|{{ill|Sanpen Inari Shrine Kofun|ja|三変稲荷神社古墳|12=draft|12=draft}}}} A {{ill|square Kofun|ja|方墳|1=Square Kofun|1=Square Kofun|12=draft|12=draft}} dated to the late 4th century. Excavated artifacts include {{ill|stone bracelets|ja|石釧|12=draft|12=draft}} and a {{ill|bronze mirror|ja|銅鏡|12=draft|12=draft}} (specifically a {{ill|Daryu Mirror|ja|鼉龍鏡|12=draft|12=draft}}). Designated a Kawagoe City {{ill|tangible cultural property|ja|有形文化財|12=draft|12=draft}}.<ref>{{Cite web|author=Kawagoe City Board of Education|url=https://www.city.kawagoe.saitama.jp/kurashi/bunkakyoyo/bunkazai/shiteibunkazai/shishiteibunkazai/sanpenninari.html|title=Sanpen Inari Shrine Kofun Excavated Artifacts|work=Kawagoe City|date=2023-12-11|accessdate=2024-04-25}}</ref>
=== Daisenba Kofun Cluster === ==== Hikawa Shrine Kofun ==== A small {{ill|round Kofun|ja|円墳|1=Round Kofun|1=Round Kofun|12=draft|12=draft}}, approximately 15 meters in diameter and 2 meters in height, located in the grounds of Senba Hikawa Shrine. Its construction date is unknown.<ref>{{Cite web|author=Kawagoe Yell|url=https://www.kawagoe-yell.com/sightseeing/hikawajinja-kohun/|title=Hikawa Shrine Kofun|work=Kawagoe Yell|accessdate=2024-04-26}}</ref>
==== Atago Shrine Kofun ==== Also known as "Chichi-zuka" (Father's Mound). A tumulus measuring 42–45 meters in diameter and 6 meters in height, topped by {{ill|Atago Shrine (Kawagoe, Saitama)|ja|愛宕神社|12=draft|12=draft}}'s shrine hall. Excavated artifacts include {{ill|stirrup fittings|ja|素環鏡板付轡|12=draft|12=draft}} and a {{ill|tachi|ja|大刀|12=draft|12=draft}}. Estimated to be built in the early 7th century.<ref>{{Cite web|author=Kawagoe City Board of Education|url=https://www.city.kawagoe.saitama.jp/kurashi/bunkakyoyo/bunkazai/shiteibunkazai/shishiteibunkazai/atagojinnjakofunn.html|title=Atago Shrine Kofun|work=Kawagoe City|date=2024-03-28|accessdate=2024-04-25}}</ref>
==== Asama Shrine Kofun ==== Also known as "Haha-zuka" (Mother's Mound). A tumulus measuring 38–35 meters in diameter and 5.75 meters in height, with {{ill|Asama Shrine (Kawagoe, Saitama)|ja|浅間神社|12=draft|12=draft}} built atop it.
